2026-05-11 | Separate Digits in an Array

	Question
Return array containing separated digits.
	Approach
1.	Traverse each number in nums  
2.	Extract digits:
		use to_string()
		OR repeated division  
3.	Add every digit to answer array
		in original order  
	Time Complexity
	O(total digits)
	Space Complexity
	O(total digits)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> separateDigits(vector<int>& nums) {
        vector<int> ans;
        for(int x : nums){
            string s = to_string(x);
            for(char c : s){
                ans.push_back(c - '0');
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
	Key Insight
Using string conversion makes:
		digit extraction simple and ordered  
This avoids reversing digits manually.
